795
01:18:24.405 --> 01:18:28.008
Still. though.
it's so fucking ugly.

796
01:18:29.143 --> 01:18:32.813
"Girls boss destroys."

797
01:18:34.181 --> 01:18:36.350
<i>Yeah. it's ugly.</i>

798
01:19:23.732 --> 01:19:26.967
I went on a date...
or I tried to.

799
01:19:29.003 --> 01:19:32.172
But I got upset. and I left.

800
01:19:38.479 --> 01:19:42.617
We're-we're supposed to talk
about work-related issues.

801
01:19:42.684 --> 01:19:45.252
Yes. I left because of a ticket.

802
01:19:45.319 --> 01:19:48.657
Okay. and what specifically
about this ticket

803
01:19:48.723 --> 01:19:51.358
made you do that?

804
01:19:51.425 --> 01:19:54.061
It bothered me.

805
01:19:54.128 --> 01:19:56.598
Can you explain why?

806
01:19:56.665 --> 01:19:59.567
Sometimes vocalizing an image

807
01:19:59.634 --> 01:20:02.336
stuck in your head
can help root it out.

808
01:20:05.005 --> 01:20:07.709
Well. you make that sound easy.

809
01:20:07.776 --> 01:20:09.511
Just give it a go.

810
01:20:12.547 --> 01:20:14.181
Um...

811
01:20:18.185 --> 01:20:22.489
Mmm. People want to hurt people.

812
01:20:25.192 --> 01:20:31.131
Okay. so in this video there
was an act of violence.

813
01:20:31.198 --> 01:20:35.269
Yes. and it made me want to
hurt someone too.

814
01:20:38.906 --> 01:20:40.974
I see.

815
01:20:41.041 --> 01:20:46.213
You know. sometimes
when I go for a run. um.

816
01:20:46.280 --> 01:20:50.518
to pump myself up. I daydream
about getting into a fight.

817
01:20:50.585 --> 01:20:54.188
defending my wife. punching
some jerk for accosting her.

818
01:20:54.254 --> 01:20:56.857
It's quite a common fantasy.
but it's not a healthy one.

819
01:20:56.924 --> 01:21:01.596
It's actually quite selfish
putting someone else
in a position of danger

820
01:21:01.663 --> 01:21:03.631
to make myself feel empowered.

821
01:21:03.698 --> 01:21:06.934
But if that actually happened.
you wouldn't be putting her
in danger.

822
01:21:06.967 --> 01:21:08.469
You'd be protecting her from it.

823
01:21:08.536 --> 01:21:11.939
Sure. but my point is.
in these situations.

824
01:21:11.972 --> 01:21:16.711
we tend to ignore the victim
and focus instead
on the villain.

825
01:21:16.778 --> 01:21:20.481
We funnel our energy
into revenge or justice

826
01:21:20.548 --> 01:21:25.953
or whatever you want to call it.
and we develop a hero complex.

827
01:21:28.088 --> 01:21:32.627
But you're not the hero here.
Daisy. This isn't some
detective story.

828
01:21:32.694 --> 01:21:35.597
You're just a regular person
doing a regular job.

829
01:21:35.663 --> 01:21:37.565
Yes. thank you.

830
01:21:37.632 --> 01:21:41.969
But maybe the girl
in the video wants that guy
to suffer like she did.

831
01:21:42.002 --> 01:21:44.972
It's what I would want.

832
01:21:48.008 --> 01:21:50.077
You have an impulse. yeah?

833
01:21:50.144 --> 01:21:52.479
To take action.
which is a wonderful thing.

834
01:21:52.547 --> 01:21:55.215
Unless that impulse is to do
something not wonderful.

835
01:21:55.282 --> 01:21:59.721
-It is not an impulse.
-What is it then?

836
01:21:59.788 --> 01:22:02.456
I try to forget. and I keep
getting reminded

837
01:22:02.524 --> 01:22:05.192
over and over.
and I know it sounds crazy.

838
01:22:05.259 --> 01:22:07.529
but it feels like the universe
is telling me:

839
01:22:07.595 --> 01:22:09.731
